=== Pipeline Stages and Model Tiering ===

|=Stage|=Name|=What Happens|=Model Tier
|1|**Extract Claims**|Two-pass extraction of atomic claims from input; Gate 1 claim validation|Haiku (budget)
|2|**Research**|Iterative web search (up to 10 rounds per claim), evidence extraction and deduplication|Haiku (budget) + Web Search
|3|**Cluster Boundaries**|Group evidence into ClaimAssessmentBoundaries by scope congruence|Haiku (budget)
|4|**Verdict**|5-step adversarial LLM debate per claim (see below)|Sonnet (standard)
|5|**Aggregate**|Weighted aggregation with triangulation, narrative generation|Sonnet (standard)

----

== Structured AI Debate ==

Every claim goes through a **adversarial debate**. Different providers argue against each other. An objection only counts as "contested" if it cites specific counter-evidence — unsupported criticism is classified as "doubted" and cannot change a verdict.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart LR
    E[Evidence + Boundaries] --> S1[1. Advocate]
    S1 --> S2[2. Self-Consistency x2]
    S1 --> S3[3. Adversarial Challenge]
    S2 --> S4[4. Reconciliation]
    S3 --> S4
    S4 --> S5[5. Validation]
    S5 --> O[Final Verdict]

    subgraph "Parallel Execution"
        S2
        S3
    end

    ANTH["Anthropic API Calls<br/>Advocate, Self-Consistency,<br/>Reconciler, Validator"]
    OPENAI["OpenAI API Call<br/>Challenger (GPT-4.1)"]

    S1 -.-> ANTH
    S2 -.-> ANTH
    S4 -.-> ANTH
    S5 -.-> ANTH
    S3 -.-> OPENAI

    style S1 fill:#e8f5e9,stroke:#2e7d32
    style S2 fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0
    style S3 fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#e65100
    style S4 fill:#f3e5f5,stroke:#7b1fa2
    style S5 fill:#fce4ec,stroke:#c2185b
    style ANTH fill:#F3E5F5,stroke:#7B1FA2,color:#4A148C,stroke-width:2px
    style OPENAI fill:#F3E5F5,stroke:#7B1FA2,color:#4A148C,stroke-width:2px
{{/mermaid}}

=== Debate Roles ===

|=Step|=Role|=Function|=Provider
|1|**Advocate**|Build the strongest evidence-backed case for the most supported interpretation|Anthropic (Sonnet)
|2|**Self-Consistency**|Two parallel re-runs at elevated temperature — measures verdict stability|Anthropic (Sonnet)
|3|**Challenger**|Adversarial challenge from a //different provider// for model diversity|OpenAI (GPT-4.1)
|4|**Reconciler**|Final verdict integrating challenge insights and stability data|Anthropic (Sonnet)
|5|**Validator**|Grounding check + direction check (advisory, non-blocking)|Anthropic (Haiku)

=== LLM Call Topology ===

|=Pipeline Part|=Typical Call Pattern
|**Stage 1: Claim extraction**|Pass 1 scan + Pass 2 evidence-grounded extraction + Gate 1 validation (batched budget-tier calls)
|**Stage 2: Research**|Repeated Haiku-tier calls for query generation, relevance classification, and evidence extraction across search rounds
|**Stage 3: Boundary clustering**|Scope normalization plus clustering calls to form ClaimAssessmentBoundaries
|**Stage 4: Verdict debate**|1 advocate + 2 self-consistency re-runs + 1 challenger + 1 reconciler + 2 lightweight validator checks
|**Stage 5: Final report**|Aggregation / narrative generation call for the published result

(% class="box infomessage" %)
(((
**Cross-provider diversity:** Steps 2 and 3 run in parallel. Using different LLM providers for Advocate vs. Challenger prevents single-model echo-chamber bias — a known weakness in single-provider fact-checking systems.
)))

----

== Verdict Transparency ==

Verdicts are not binary. The system reports a **7-point scale** with confidence levels, so you know whether a claim is overwhelmingly supported, genuinely mixed, or contradicted — and how confident the system is.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart LR
    TRUE["TRUE\n86-100%"]
    MT["MOSTLY\nTRUE\n72-85%"]
    LT["LEANING\nTRUE\n58-71%"]
    MIXED["MIXED /\nUNVERIFIED\n43-57%"]
    LF["LEANING\nFALSE\n29-42%"]
    MF["MOSTLY\nFALSE\n15-28%"]
    FALSE["FALSE\n0-14%"]

    TRUE --- MT --- LT --- MIXED --- LF --- MF --- FALSE

    style TRUE fill:#2e7d32,color:#fff
    style MT fill:#43a047,color:#fff
    style LT fill:#66bb6a,color:#000
    style MIXED fill:#fdd835,color:#000
    style LF fill:#ff9800,color:#000
    style MF fill:#e65100,color:#fff
    style FALSE fill:#b71c1c,color:#fff
{{/mermaid}}

Each verdict includes: truth percentage, confidence tier (High / Medium / Low / Insufficient evidence), supporting and opposing evidence citations, and a full reasoning narrative.

----

== Evidence Quality: Defence in Depth ==

Every piece of evidence passes through **six layers of quality control** before it can influence a verdict. Two phases: pre-verdict evidence quality filtering and post-verdict verdict quality validation.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart TB
    RAW["Raw Evidence\n(from LLM extraction)"]

    subgraph P1["Phase 1: Evidence Quality (Pre-Verdict)"]
        L1["LLM Prompt Instructions\n(guide extraction quality)"]
        L2["Deterministic Filter\n(min length, vague phrases, dedup,\ncategory rules, probative scoring)"]
        L3["Provenance Validation\n(reject synthetic/LLM-generated content)"]
    end

    subgraph P2["Phase 2: Verdict Quality (Post-Verdict)"]
        L4["Source Reliability Weighting\n(domain credibility 0.0-1.0)"]
        L5["Aggregation Pruning\n(tangential, opinion-only,\ncontestation validation)"]
        L6["Validator Checks\n(grounding + direction,\nwarn-only by default)"]
    end

    CLEAN["Published Report\n(verdict + warnings)"]

    RAW --> L1 --> L2 --> L3 --> L4 --> L5 --> L6 --> CLEAN

    style RAW fill:#ffcdd2,stroke:#b71c1c,color:#000
    style CLEAN fill:#c8e6c9,stroke:#2e7d32,color:#000
    style P1 fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0,color:#000
    style P2 fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f9a825,color:#000
    style L1 fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0,color:#000
    style L2 fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0,color:#000
    style L3 fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0,color:#000
    style L4 fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f9a825,color:#000
    style L5 fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f9a825,color:#000
    style L6 fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f9a825,color:#000
{{/mermaid}}

Source reliability scores are computed per-domain using multi-provider LLM evaluation, with cross-check refinement and persistent caching. A peer-reviewed study carries different weight than a social media post — automatically.

