== Target User Groups ==

|=User Group|=How They Use FactHarbor|=Key Need
|**General Public**|Browse published analyses, explore the evidence landscape — no registration required|Transparent, accessible verdicts they can verify themselves
|**Journalists & Content Creators**|Fact-check claims before publishing; cite FactHarbor verdicts with full provenance|API access, speed, credibility — evidence chains they can reference in their work
|**Researchers & Academics**|Filter by verification status, confidence levels, source quality; export data for studies|Audit trails, reproducible results, exportable structured data
|**Social Media Users**|Quick-check claims before sharing to avoid spreading misinformation|Fast turnaround, clear verdicts, easy to understand
|**Educators**|Use real-world claim analyses as teaching material for critical thinking and media literacy|Multi-perspective evidence landscapes, not just binary verdicts

(% class="box infomessage" %)
(((
**Design principle:** Low barrier to entry — anyone can browse without registration. Submission requires only a free account. Every verdict is fully transparent: cited evidence, source reliability scores, and documented debate reasoning.
)))

