== Open-Source Goals: Contributors & Sponsors ==

FactHarbor is a **non-profit, open-source** project. Sustainability depends on building a community and securing institutional support:

=== Contributors ===

|=Goal|=Why
|**Academic contributors**|Researchers integrate evaluation metrics, benchmark new techniques, publish on the platform
|**Developer community**|Open-source contributors build browser extensions, API clients, CMS plugins, language support
|**Fact-checking organizations**|Professional fact-checkers improve analysis quality, contribute domain expertise, validate verdicts
|**Student projects**|Bachelor/Master theses on specific pipeline components (evidence retrieval, debate patterns, multilingual robustness)

=== Sponsors & Funding ===

|=Goal|=Why
|**Research grants (Innosuisse, SNSF, EU Horizon)**|Fund postdoc positions and research collaborations — this is the path we are exploring today
|**Foundation grants**|Media foundations, digital democracy initiatives, press freedom organizations
|**Institutional partnerships**|Universities, libraries, public broadcasters — credibility and reach
|**Infrastructure sponsors**|Cloud credits, LLM API credits (Anthropic, OpenAI NPO programs) — the primary operational cost

